Class MrqLocationService

  • java.lang.Object

          • com.mobilerq.android.sdk.MrqLocationService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.content.ComponentCallbacks, android.content.ComponentCallbacks2

    public class MrqLocationService
extends android.app.Service
    MrqLocationService is a service that monitors location changes for the device. It can be used by calling the startMonitoringLocation() methods. Once the service is started, it will continue running until stopMonitoringLocation() is called.

    MrqLocationService makes use of the Google Play SDK.
